	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Your best bet is to find the original Japanese ROM, then apply a patch to it.  Lots of sites with pre-patched ROMs will have really old, incomplete, and/or buggy versions.  Sites that only have patches usually care enough to keep the latest/best version.
<br />
<br />You can find patches here:
<br /><a href="http://www.romhacking.net/" class="postlink">http://www.romhacking.net/</a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


